        <fr:title text="Lawvere-Tierney topology for closed subtopoi">Lawvere-Tierney topology for closed subtopoi</fr:title>
        <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {X}]]></fr:tex> be a topos, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi ]]></fr:tex> a subterminal object. The <html:em>closed subtopos</html:em> associated with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi ]]></fr:tex> has the Lawvere-Tierney operator as 
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ c_{\varphi } = (-) \vee  \varphi  : \Omega  \to  \Omega . ]]></fr:tex></html:p>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
      <fr:frontmatter>
        <fr:authors />
        <fr:date>
          <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
          <fr:month>6</fr:month>
          <fr:day>9</fr:day>
        </fr:date>
        <fr:source-path>/Users/xielingyuan/Documents/GitHub/logical-geometry/trees/topology/topl-6LIP.tree</fr:source-path>
        <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/topl-6LIP/</fr:uri>
        <fr:display-uri>topl-6LIP</fr:display-uri>
        <fr:route>/topl-6LIP/</fr:route>
        <fr:title text="Reflector for closed subtopoi">Reflector for closed subtopoi</fr:title>
        <fr:taxon>Construction</fr:taxon>
      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[c_\varphi ]]></fr:tex> be the <fr:link href="/topl-R1F1/" title="Lawvere-Tierney topology for closed subtopoi" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-R1F1/" display-uri="topl-R1F1" type="local">closed Lawvere-Tierney operator</fr:link> associated with a subterminal <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi ]]></fr:tex> of a topos <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {X}]]></fr:tex>. This way, a subobject <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U \rightarrowtail  Y]]></fr:tex> is <html:em>dense</html:em> iff the following holds in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {X}]]></fr:tex>,
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ \forall  y \in  Y.\  \varphi  \vee  y \in  U. ]]></fr:tex>
  This induces a <html:em>closed monad</html:em> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {X}]]></fr:tex>
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ \Diamond _\varphi  : \mathcal {X} \to  \mathcal {X} ]]></fr:tex>
  where for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X\in \mathcal {X}]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Diamond _\varphi  X]]></fr:tex> is the following pushout,
  
  <html:figure><fr:resource hash="e06cb087e7cc6790de259d8bb02c40cd"><fr:resource-content><html:img src="/e06cb087e7cc6790de259d8bb02c40cd.svg" /></fr:resource-content><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="preamble"><![CDATA[\usepackage {tikz-cd}\usepackage {quiver}]]></fr:resource-source><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="body"><![CDATA[
    \begin {tikzcd}
      X \times  \varphi  \ar [r] \ar [d] & \varphi  \ar [d] \\ 
      X \ar [r] & \Diamond _\varphi  X 
      \arrow ["\lrcorner "{anchor = center, pos = 0.125, rotate=180}, draw = none, from=2-2, to=1-1]
    \end {tikzcd}
  ]]></fr:resource-source></fr:resource></html:figure>

  It turns out that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is closed for this monad iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X^\varphi  \cong  1]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
      </fr:mainmatter>
